doc.ContractDescription: FPDS BASE DESCRIPTION, MULTIPLE YEAR AWARD AND INCREMENTAL FUNDING FOR YEARS 1 OF 5. THIS PROPOSAL IS ENTITLED, "FOUNDATIONS OF COMPLEX LIFE: EVOLUTION, PRESERVATION AND DETECTION ON EARTH AND BEYOND." THIS IS AWARDED IN RESPONSE TO COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT NOTICE (CAN) NO. NNH12ZDA002C, (NAI), CYCLE SIX. THE PRINCIPAL INVESTIGATOR IS ROGER E. SUMMONS WITH MASSACHUSETTS INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY (MIT). BASIC COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT SPECIAL CONDITION COLLABORATION STATEMENT: 1260.51 COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT SPECIAL CONDITION. (OCTOBER 2000) (A) THIS AWARD IS A COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT AS IT IS ANTICIPATED THERE WILL BE SUBSTANTIAL NASA INVOLVEMENT DURING PERFORMANCE OF THE EFFORT. NASA AND THE RECIPIENT MUTUALLY AGREE TO THE FOLLOWING STATEMENT OF ANTICIPATED COOPERATIVE INTERACTIONS WHICH MAY OCCUR DURING THE PERFORMANCE OF THIS EFFORT: THE NASA ASTROBIOLOGY INSTITUTE (NAI) DIRECTOR AND NAI CENTRAL ARE HOUSED AT NASA AMES RESEARCH CENTER, NASA'S LEAD CENTER FOR ASTROBIOLOGY. NAI CENTRAL IS RESPONSIBLE FOR COORDINATING INSTITUTE ACTIVITIES, ADVOCATING THE NEEDS AND SCIENTIFIC INTERESTS OF THE MEMBERS OF THIS COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT, DISBURSING FUNDS (INCLUDING A STRATEGIC DIRECTOR'S DISCRETIONARY FUND (DDF) FOR HIGH-RISK/HIGH-PAYOFF RESEARCH PROJECTS AND FOR FOSTERING COLLABORATION BETWEEN MEMBERS), SPONSORING THE NAI POSTDOCTORAL FELLOWSHIP PROGRAM, COLLECTING AND ARCHIVING INFORMATION ON RESEARCH ACCOMPLISHMENTS AND PUBLICATIONS, ORGANIZING FOCUS GROUP MEETINGS AND WORKSHOPS, AND EXPEDITING NETWORK CONNECTIVITY WHILE ENGINEERING THE INTERFACES BETWEEN THE SCIENTISTS AND THE NETWORK. NAI CENTRAL IS ALSO RESPONSIBLE FOR ORGANIZING GENERAL MEETINGS, WORKSHOPS, AND STRATEGIC RETREATS TO ENGAGE MEMBERS OF THE INSTITUTE IN INTEGRATED RESEARCH. NAI CENTRAL WILL, IN ADDITION, COORDINATE INSTITUTE-WIDE ACTIVITIES, IN EDUCATION AND PUBLIC OUTREACH, AND IN THE TRAINING OF STUDENTS AND OTHER YOUNG INVESTIGATORS. MEMBERS OF THE NIA/MIT TEAM, THROUGH THIS COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT, WILL: ACTIVELY PURSUE ITS RESEARCH PROGRAM; PARTICIPATE IN INSTITUTE ACTIVITIES SUCH AS WORKSHOPS, SEMINARS, FOCUS GROUPS, CLASSES, TRAINING, AND EDUCATION AND PUBLIC OUTREACH; CONTRIBUTE TO NASA SCIENCE WORKING GROUPS AND ANALYSIS COMMITTEES; AND WORK CONTINUOUSLY TO IMPROVE THE EFFECTIVENESS OF THE INTER-MEMBER CONNECTIONS AND COLLABORATIONS. THE PI OF LEAD TEAM, AS A MEMBER OF THE NIA EXECUTIVE COUNCIL, WILL MEET BY VIDEO-CON ON A MONTHLY BASIS IN PERSON THREE OR FOUR TIMES ANNUALLY. THE PI WILL PARTICIPATE VIA THE EXECUTIVE COUNCIL AS THE PRIMARY TECHNICAL GUIDING BODY OF THE INSTITUTE. LEAD INSTITUTION SITES WILL BE EQUIPPED WITH NASA DEPLOYED VIDEOCONFERENCING SYSTEMS THAT ENABLE TEAM PRINCIPAL INVESTIGATORS TO ATTEND MONTHLY EXECUTIVE COUNCIL MEETINGS AND TO CONFER WITH ONE ANOTHER, WITH NAI MANAGEMENT AT AMES, AND WITH NASA HQ PERSONNEL. THESE CONFERENCING SYSTEMS ARE ALSO TO BE UTILIZED FOR A VARIETY OF OTHER PURPOSES BY NAI MEMBERS LOCATED AT THE LEAD INSTITUTIONS, INCLUDING JOINT PRESENTATIONS OF CLASSES, SEMINARS, AND SCIENTIFIC EXCHANGE. PROJECT SUMMARY: WE WILL COMBINE OUR SCIENTIFIC RESEARCH WITH A ROBUST PROGRAM OF EDUCATIONAL ACTIVITIES AND OUTREACH TO THE GENERAL PUBLIC THAT WILL INCLUDE AFTER-SCHOOL SCIENCE CURRICULA, DEVELOPMENT OF UNDERGRADUATE RESOURCES, PARTICIPATION IN LOCAL AND DISTRICT ACTIVITIES SUCH AS THE CAMBRIDGE SCIENCE FESTIVAL, OUTREACH TRAINING FOR TEAM MEMBERS, AND CONTINUED INVOLVEMENT WITH OTHER NAI TEAMS IN CONDUCTING WORKSHOPS WITHOUT WALLS AND IN THE DEVELOPMENT OF VIRTUAL FIELD TRIPS.

doc.ContractDescription: ANNUAL MAINTENANCE AND SOFTWARE UPDATES TO ENSURE THAT THEY REMAIN RELIABLE AND CAPABLE OF SUCCESSFULLY SUPPORTING ELSUR OPERATION.

ON THE EFFICIENCY OF MAGNETIC RECONNECTION AT THE MAGNETOPAUSE. WHEN THE RECONNECTION RATE IS HIGH, LARGE AMOUNTS OF ENERGY AND MASS ARE TRANSFERRED FROM THE SOLAR WIND TO THE MAGNETOSPHERE. THE PLASMASPHERIC PLUME IS ONE FEATURE THAT MAY LIMIT THIS THE OVERARCHING GOAL OF THIS STUDY IS TO QUANTIFY HOW THE PLASMASPHERIC PLUME IMPACTS RECONNECTION AND SOLAR WIND-MAGNETOSPHERIC COUPLING. COUPLING PROCESS. DURING GEOMAGNETICALLY QUITE TIMES, THE POPULATION OF COLD, DENSE, CHARGED PARTICLES COMPOSING THE PLASMASPHERE EXB DRIFT ON CLOSED PATHS WITHIN A RADIAL DISTANCE OF ....... 4.5 RE AROUND THE EARTH. DMING MORE DISTURBED TIMES OF STRONG SOLAR WIND DRIVING, AN ENHANCED CONVECTION ELECTRIC FIELD CAN CAUSE SOME OF THE DENSE PLASMASPHERE TO FORM A TONGUE OR PLUME EXTENDING SUNWARD TOWARDS THE DAYSIDE MAGNETOPAUSE. WHEN THE PLUME IS IN THE VICINITY OF THE SUBSOLAR MAGNETOPAUSE, THE DENSITY CAN INCREASE FROM A NOMINAL VALUE OF ,...,0 .L CM 3 BY THREE ORDERS OF MAGNITUDE TO ,..., 100 CM 3 . THEORY PREDICTS THE LOCAL RECONNECTION RATE TO BE INVERSELY PROPORTIONAL TO .J DENSITY. ALL OTHER VARIABLES REMAINING THE SAME, INCREASING THE DENSITY BY LOOOX FROM THE PRESENCE OF THE PLUME WOULD DECREASE THE MAGNETOPAUSE RECONNECTION RATE BY A FACTOR OF 32. AN EQUALLY IMPORTANT ASPECT OF THIS ISSUE TO BE ADDRESSED IN THIS STUDY IS SPATIALLY BOW LARGE IS A PLUME AS IT CONTACTS THE MAGNETOPAUSE? DECREASING THE RECONNECTION RATE BY SUCH A DEGREE WOULD HAVE A SIGNIFICANT IMPACT ON THE TRANSFER OF ENERGY FROM THE SOLAR WIND TO THE MAGNETOSPHERE. THIS WOULD LIMIT THE GENERATION OF STORMS, SUBSTORMS, AS WELL AS OTHER GEOMAGNETIC DISTURBANCES. A PLUME WOULD ALSO BE ACTIVE IN CONTROLLING HOW GEOEFFECTIVE CERTAIN SOLAR WIND STRUCTURES ARE. IN ADDITION TO THE GLOBAL MAGNETOSPHERIC PICTURE, THIS PROBLEM ALSO PROVIDES A USEFUL PLATFO1M TO STUDY THE MICROPHYSICS OF RECONNECTION. THE CUFFENT STUDY WILL MONITOR CHANGES IN RECONNECTION AND OTHER FORMS OF SOLAR WIND-MAGNETOSPHERE COUPLING WITH THE THEMIS SPACECRAFT. CAREFUL INSPECTION OF MAGNETOPAUSE OF SOLAR WIND-MAGNETOSPHERE COUPLING WITH AND WITHOUT HIGH DENSITY PLUME MATERIAL WILL ALLOW THE TEAM TO STUDY THE IMPACT OF CHANGING DENSITY SEVERAL ORDERS OF MAGNITUDE ON THESE MECHANISMS. THE STUDY IS TIMELY AS IT PROVIDES IMPORTANT INPUT FOR UNDERSTANDING THE VAN ALLEN PROBE AND THEMIS DATA. SINCE A PLUME CAN CUT ACROSS ALL L-SHELLS, WAVES THAT OCCUR PREFERENTIALLY FOR HIGH DENSITY SUCH AS PLASMASPHERIC HISS, WHISTLER-MODE CHORUS, AND EMIC CAN ENERGIZE AND SCATTER RADIATION BELT PARTICLES OVER A WIDE RADIAL RANGE. THE PROPOSED STUDY ALSO ADDRESSES GOALS OF THE FORTHCOMING MMS MISSION TO UNDERSTAND HOW EFFICIENT RECONNECTION IS UNDER GREATLY DIFFERENT PLASMA REGIMES WITH AND WITHOUT HIGBDENSITY PLUMES.
